# Chimera Evaluation Alert Configuration
# Copy this file to docker/env.evaluation and fill in your values

# ===================================================================
# IMPORTANT SECURITY NOTICE
# ===================================================================
# NEVER commit actual tokens to version control!
# This file is in .gitignore to prevent accidental commits
# Rotate tokens every 30-90 days for best security practices

# ===================================================================
# TELEGRAM BOT NOTIFICATIONS
# ===================================================================
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Open Telegram and search for @BotFather
# 2. Send /newbot and follow the prompts to create a bot
# 3. Copy the bot token (format: 123456789:ABCdefGHIjklMNOpqrsTUVwxyz)
# 4. Search for @userinfobot or @getidsbot in Telegram
# 5. Send /start to get your chat ID

# Telegram Bot Authentication Token
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456789:ABCdefGHIjklMNOpqrsTUVwxyz

# Telegram Chat ID (number for private chats, negative for groups)
TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=123456789

# ===================================================================
# DISCORD WEBHOOK NOTIFICATIONS
# ===================================================================
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Open your Discord server settings
# 2. Go to Integrations → Webhooks
# 3. Click "Create Webhook" or "New Webhook"
# 4. Copy the webhook URL
# 5. Customize the webhook name and avatar if desired

# Discord Webhook URL (format: https://discord.com/api/webhooks/...)
DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL=https://discord.com/api/webhooks/123456789012345678/ABCdefGHIjklMNOpqrsTUVwxyz

# ===================================================================
# NOTIFICATION RULES
# ===================================================================
# The Chimera system sends notifications for the following events:
#
# Critical Events (always sent):
#   • Circuit breaker triggered
#   • Wallet drained (significant balance drop)
#   • RPC fallback activated
#   • Critical system failures
#
# Important Events (rate-limited to 1 per minute):
#   • Position exited with PnL
#   • High latency detected
#   • Database connection issues
#   • Queue depth warnings
#
# Informational Events (rate-limited to 1 per 5 minutes):
#   • Wallet promoted to ACTIVE status
#   • Daily performance summaries
#   • System health status updates
#   • Evaluation milestones reached

# ===================================================================
# TESTING NOTIFICATIONS
# ===================================================================
# After configuring tokens, test notifications:
# 1. Run the setup helper: ./ops/setup-alert-tokens.sh
# 2. Check anomaly detection logs: docker logs chimera-anomaly-detector
# 3. Trigger a test alert (if implemented): curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/test-alert
# 4. Monitor for incoming notifications on Telegram/Discord

# ===================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ===================================================================
# If notifications aren't working:
# 1. Verify tokens are correct (no extra spaces or characters)
# 2. Check bot permissions (Telegram bot must be added to chat/group)
# 3. Test webhook URL works in Discord (should show green checkmark)
# 4. Check container logs: docker logs chimera-anomaly-detector
# 5. Verify network connectivity from containers
# 6. Test with @userinfobot that your chat ID is correct

# ===================================================================
# ADVANCED CONFIGURATION
# ===================================================================
# For custom notification behavior, you can also configure:
#   • Custom alert thresholds in ops/detect-anomalies.py
#   • Notification rate limits in config.yaml
#   • Additional notification channels in operator/src/notifications/
#   • Custom message templates in operator/src/notifications/telegram.rs